8. Users' rights under GDPR or equivalent laws and regulations
8.1 If you fall under the provision of GDPR or equivalent provisions, you have the following rights with respect to the processing of your personal data. To exercise any of the following rights, you can send a request to the contact listed under "Contact".
We may ask you to provide certain information in order to identify and correct your data.
(1) Right to withdraw consent
You have the right to withdraw your consent at any time in accordance with Article 7(3) of the GDPR. If you wish to withdraw your consent, please contact the contact person set forth in Policy. This withdrawal of consent will not affect the legality of the treatment based on the consent before its withdrawal. If you withdraw your consent, you may not continue to use Application or Game Service.
(2) Rights of access and modification
You have the right under Article 15 of the GDPR to confirm whether your personal data is being processed and, if so, to access your personal data. Additionally, under Article 16 of the GDPR, you have the right to obtain the rectification of any inaccurate personal data concerning you without undue delay.
(3) Right of elimination and right of restriction on processing
Pursuant to Article 17 of the GDPR, you have the right to obtain from us the erasure of personal data concerning you without undue delay.
You also have the right to restrict the processing of your personal data in accordance with Article 18 of the GDPR.
However, we may deny your request or postpone our response if your personal information is legitimately used to provide our services or for other purposes.
(3) Right to data portability
Pursuant to Article 20 of the GDPR, you have the right to receive the personal data provided to us in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format and to have these data transmitted to another controller without hindrance from us to whom the personal data were provided. You also have the right to have your personal data transmitted directly from us to another company, where technically feasible.
(4) Right of objection
Pursuant to Article 21 of the GDPR, you have the right to object at any time to the processing of personal data concerning you for reasons related to your particular situation. In such cases, we will respond diligently in accordance with the relevant laws and regulations.
(5) Right to file a complaint with the supervisory authority
Pursuant to Article 77 of the GDPR, if you believe that the processing of personal data concerning you is in breach of this regulation without prejudice to any other administrative or judicial remedy, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority, particularly in the Member State of your habitual residence, place of work, or place where the breach is suspected.
8.2Transfer of Personal Information
We may transfer and process your personal data from your country or region of residence to Japan and other countries around the world. We may share your information with international organizations as partners. Please note that these countries or jurisdictions may not have the same data protection laws as your country.
9. Secure management of personal information
We strive to protect personal information by implementing appropriate and reasonable levels of information security management measures to prevent the loss, destruction, alteration, damage, leakage, etc. of personal information. When outsourcing the handling of personal information to outside parties, we strongly request that they comply with applicable personal information protection laws and sign a confidentiality agreement to maintain confidentiality.
While we will always use our best efforts to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee or represent that your information is completely protected.
